[[File:JacenJaina-PlagueStorehouse-YJK11.jpg|thumb|right|300px|Jedi trainees [[Jaina Solo Fel|Jaina]] and [[Darth Caedus|Jacen Solo]] among several plague canisters in the [[Emperor's plague storehouse]].]]
The '''Emperor's Plague''' was a mutagenic plague developed by [[Evir Derricote]] that only [[Death/Legends|killed]] [[Human/Legends|Humans]]. It was more deadly than the [[Krytos virus]] which killed millions of [[Alien/Legends|aliens]] on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] following the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] [[Liberation of Coruscant (Galactic Civil War)|capture]] of [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] in [[6 ABY/Legends|6 ABY]]. It was said to be so horrible that even [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]] feared to deploy it.

This plague was stored at an uncharted [[Asteroid/Legends|asteroid]] known as the [[Emperor's plague storehouse]]. In [[24 ABY/Legends|24 ABY]], a sample of it was obtained by an [[Information broker/Legends|information broker]], [[Fonterrat]], who sold it to [[Nolaa Tarkona]]. During the [[Battle of the Emperor's Plague Storehouse]], a team of [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]], with [[Bornan Thul]], destroyed all canisters containing the disease along with other alien-specific plagues, stopping the [[Diversity Alliance]]'s genocidal [[Anti-Humanism|anti-human]] crusade.

